T*
(- Pronunciation should first be understood as a language idea before it is treated as an) Tj
T*
(exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand stress, vowel sounds, consonants, and clear articulation) Tj
T*
(because it controls how questions in Pronunciation are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Pronunciation uses the correct interpretation or writing method and) Tj
T*
(explains why that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Contrasting minimal pairs with different vowel sounds is the type of application that) Tj
T*
(helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Pronunciation.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind stress, vowel sounds,) Tj
T*
(consonants, and clear articulation.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct interpretation or writing method step by step instead of jumping to) Tj
T*
(the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
