(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on contrasting minimal pairs with different vowel sounds.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in stress, vowel sounds, consonants, and clear articulation) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Pronunciation step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on stress patterns and sound distinctions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid pronouncing words only by spelling while solving it.) Tj
